2023 스프링 메이크업 트렌드는 ‘글로우 메이크업’ 마스크 벗고 다니니까 글로우템들 맘껏 쓸 수 있잖아요? 그래서 보여드리는 #맥 #글로우스택 메이크업 루틴💓
이름 그대로 글로우한 친구들 하나씩 쌓아가는 과정이 참 재밌습니다. 맥 틴티드 프라이머는 원래도 추천템이지만ㅎㅎㅎ 스킨케어 라인들도 넘 좋더라고용. 그리고 립스틱도 다들 촉촉이..!! 메이크업 완성 룩에는 맥 BEST 립밤인 텐더토크 립밤 플레이 위드 미 컬러 발라줬어요. 쉬어한 레드 컬러라 요기조기 잘 어울린답니다! 말캉폭신한 신기한 제형의 마시멜로우 블러쉬는 치키 데블 컬러! 손으로 톡톡 발라주는 거 추천해요. 텁텁함 없이 가볍고 예뿌게 발려서 눈두덩이에도 슥슥 발라주기 좋답니다..💓 올 봄에는 트렌디하게 글로우~~~한 메이크업 즐겨보쟈구!

#제품증정광고 레이어드 할 수록 화사하게, 
맑게 빛나는 나만의 글로우 레이어링
#맥 #글로우스택 메이크업 ༉·₊˚✧

2023년 맥이 제안하는
스프링 메이크업 트렌드 키워드 #글로우메이크업 !!

이제 마스크도 시원하게 벗었겠다~
마음놓고, 마스크 묻어남 걱정 할 필요 없이
마음껏 글로우 메이크업을 즐길 때가 왔습니다 여러분.

글로우 메이크업 성공 꿀TIP은,
일단 글로우하게 차오르는 스킨케어와 베이스 메이크업!
맥에서 제안하는 글로우 메이크업 Step1.
#핑크톤업워터 라이트풀 C3 래디언트 하이드레이션 스킨 리뉴얼 로션으로
피부 톤은 맑게 케어해주고, 피부 결도 부드럽게 정돈해주는데요!

Step2. 세럼과 모이스처라이저가 결합되어 피부 장벽 강화 + 톤결 개선에 도움을 주는
#꽃잎세럼 하이퍼 리얼 세라마이저TM 스킨 밸런싱 하이드레이션 세럼으로 
완벽한 피부 캔버스 만들어주기!

Step3. 글로우 메이크업을 극대화 해줄 #로즈톤업베이스 
라이트풀 C+ 코랄 그라스 틴티드 프라이머로 들뜸 없는 피부 메이크업 완성~~
높은 자외선 차단 기능 덕분에 따로 자외선 차단제를 바를 필요 없어서 더 좋아요!

Step4. 화사한 글로시 메이크업을 완성할 수 있는
✔️ #텐더토크립밤 플레이 위드 미
✔️ #글로우플레이립밤 플로랄 코랄
✔️ #러스터글래스립스틱 씨 쉬어, 노 포토스, 셀아웃
✔️ #글로우플레이블러쉬 치키 데블로 생기를 더해주세요!

마지막으로 대즐 섀도우와 미네랄라이즈 스킨 피니쉬의
쉬머펄로 존재감 있는 글로우를 더해주면 끝!
곧 메이크업도 보여드릴게요

Számomra a #oneandonly rúzs a MAC-től az Angel árnyalat. Zseniális az állaga és tökéletesen passzol hozzám ez a szín.
Sokszor kerestem az utódját, de valahogy sosem találtam meg azt a verziót, ami picit más árnyalat, de hasonló hatást kelt. Mostanáig!🤩
A #MACbyRichardQuinn kollekció lenyűgöző, virágos, tavaszi csomagolást kapott. Leginkább a letisztult külsőt kedvelem a MAC termékeiben, de ez a kollekció már annyira sok, hogy ettől csodálatos. Bevallom nem sok információm volt a brit tervezőről, nem ismertem a munkáit, de miután rákerestem és megláttam az alkotásait, leesett az állam. Érdemes végigpörgetnetek az Instagram oldalát (@richardquinn ) és, ha már ott vagytok, nézzétek meg a @lindaevangelista -ról készült fotót is. Mennyei! ✨ Ezek után egészen más szemmel néztem ezt a kollekciót, melyben gyönyörű élénk színekkel ellátott palettát, eszméletlen szép rúzsokat, rózsa mintában csillogó highlighter-t, menta és levendula színű szemceruzát, csodás virágos Fix+-t és egy sunset boulevard 😭🥰 névre keresztelt pirosítót is találtok. 
Az árnyalat amit viselek a Rose Daydream 🌹

Some assorted shots from Manzini, Eswatini's most populous city, and the one closest to the international airport.

The downtown area consists mainly of a bunch of newish shopping centers nestled along some rolling green hills.

It's light on tourist sites, and the cityscape is not the most distinct, but Manzini felt cleaner, more developed, and more well-lit than most of the smaller African cities I have been to.

“De um lado, a construção de um senso de desimportância e despertencimento, do outro, o fortalecimento subjetivo e o pacto narcísico. Assim, o racismo estrutura relações hierárquicas que se fortalecem a partir de microagressões cotidianas. O amor romântico dará sua contribuição construindo a ideia de “toda loira tem a sua morena”, exatamente como a alma-gêmea cristã, deixando cada peça “em seu devido lugar”.

Nós conhecemos bem este enredo: orbitar a protagonista branca tem como principal característica o exercício de uma escuta reforçadora e conselheira. Sabemos que mulheres brancas herdaram das sinhás o ideal de ego fortalecido acobertado pelo véu da fragilidade. E é quando emprestamos a nossa energia espiritual para servi-las uma escuta que pouco questiona e sempre acolhe que ganhamos sua atenção. Apenas neste momento, por isso o senso de desimportância e despertencimento. Se não temos lugar para nos expressar livremente e contribuir com os dons que trouxemos ao mundo, adoecemos. Não é à toa que muitas de nós carrega consigo a crença no abandono e na substituição.

Assim como os lugares de perseguidor e perseguido, o racismo também constrói a admiradora e admirada. Isso nada tem a ver com rivalidade feminina, mas sim com a manutenção de um ideal de ego que, quando confrontado, poderá ser explicado pela inveja. Esta, só pode existir se há um sujeito desejando possuir o que não lhe pertence. Afinal de contas, na meritocracia, o segundo lugar indica não ser bom o suficiente. Back during indoor season I got asked “why are you still pole vaulting? Do you think you think you can still improve?” At first I was hurt by that because yea I’m 30 and no I haven’t jumped that high in a while. But then I realized that yeah I actually do have a lot to improve on. Working with Tray we’ve made the conscious decision to work on bad habits that I’ve had for a long time. Now I’m jumping better than I ever have. I’m practicing extremely well, moving more weight in the weight room and I have more speed then ever. 
I don’t know if y’all know this but early 30’s for women is their athletic prime!
.
Honestly though I’m still pole vaulting because I want to.

“Amas-me? Perguntou Alice. Não, não te amo! Respondeu o Coelho Branco. Alice franziu a testa e juntou as mãos como fazia sempre que se sentia ferida. Vês? Retorquiu o Coelho Branco. Agora vais começar a perguntar-te o que te torna tão imperfeita e o que fizeste de mal para que eu não consiga amar-te pelo menos um pouco. Sabes, é por esta razão que não te posso amar. Nem sempre serás amada Alice, haverá dias em que os outros estarão cansados e aborrecidos com a vida, terão a cabeça nas nuvens e irão magoar-te. Porque as pessoas são assim, de algum modo sempre acabam por ferir os sentimentos uns dos outros, seja por descuido, incompreensão ou conflitos consigo mesmos. Se tu não te amares, ao menos um pouco, se não crias uma couraça de amor próprio e de felicidade ao redor do teu Coração, os débeis dissabores causados pelos outros tornar-se-ão letais e destruir-te-ão. A primeira vez que te vi fiz um pacto comigo mesmo: "Evitarei amar-te até aprenderes a amar-te a ti mesma!"

Alice No País das Maravilhas

Anambra State Governor, Chukwuma Soludo, has tasked the newly inaugurated members of the Anambra State Internal Revenue Service to increase the state’s internally generated revenue, describing the agency as the lifeblood of every government.

Soludo disclosed this on Monday during the inauguration of members of the board at the Governor’s Lodge, Amawbia.

The governor reminded them that the state has yet to start generating up to 3 billion naira a month on IGR and that an over 180 percent turnaround on the state revenue is required as the 2023 budget depends on it.

In like manner, the Board of Anambra State Housing Development Corporation were inaugurated with a charge to bring about a positive disruptive change in the sector and bridge the gap of millions of housing deficit in the state.

The board chaired by former Deputy Governor of Anambra, Emeka Sibeudu, was also mandated to develop housing structures that would suit the desires of the people.

The chairman pledged complete commitment to disruptive change in the state’s housing development.

caption:
My Gorgeous Bride Ro who looked absolutely gorgeous on her wedding day. I posted a short of her on my YouTube channel and it got 43k views , wow that's was 🤪. I did her trial and we did a soft natural look for her. On the wedding day her bridesmaids went for Natural Glam Charlotte tilbury vibes and she changed her mind. She wanted the Glam kind of look her bridesmaids went for. It's very important for a bride to feel and look her best on the day. This can only be done if you have confidence in your hair and makeup artist. I get brides all the time who change their minds last minute and nothing makes me happier than thinking they have this confidence in me . We changed the look to what bridesmaids were going for and Ro was really happy. 

 I am so behind posting content just not feeling to post anything. But I have so many pics so better start posting before 2023 bride and bridesmaids take over my insta excited to receive so many inquiries for 2023
And thankyou to those who have confirmed already. 😘😘

A little bit of my makeup background.

I recently discovered cosmetics in September of last year, so if the math is correct I started 6 months ago. I started out with just an eyeliner pencil because eyeliner is what grabbed my attention more so than any other product. I really admire/admired the cat eye look, as well as the ancient Egypt type look. For a while I just wanted the eyeliner and didn’t think I would proceed and broaden my makeup horizons. As time progressed I gradually discovered new and exciting products. Bronzer, lipstick, mascara, false lashes, eyeshadow, highlighter, foundations, powders, blushes, primers, etc. I feel I have made tremendous progress throughout my makeup journey and have come a long way. I can’t wait to share it all with you!

102 weeks dye free // I just got hired for my first paid job as a professional makeup artist and I’m so excited to embark on this new career path. I used MAC skincare products on my face which is still healing from an #intensepulsedlight skin rejuvenation treatment 4 days ago. My cheeks are still a bit swollen and pink as this is where the most pigment was targeted due to dilated capillaries & sun damage. And yes, I’m absolutely not knowledgeable when it comes to makeup. Happy April Fool’s Day! I was just having fun with some MAC Cosmetics after work. I’m not adept at doing eye makeup at 53 so I often skip it for the most part, focusing on cheek and lip colors. I usually air dry my hair for beach waves but brushed it out to show the greys which are often hidden underneath my top hair layers. My hair gets so big when it’s brushed dry. 😆 I used #macstackmascara which is this week’s #mactrend #permedlashes .  My attempt at eyeshadow is weak but I was just having fun experimenting with colors I usually wear separately #macallthatglitters and #macembark . The purple eyeshadow was my first ever MAC purchase years ago as a MUA told me to just use it as a soft eyeliner using a thin brush since I told him that I’m makeup challenged. It actually looks quite neutral on an otherwise bare lid. Happy April 1. Enjoy this life cause you only get one. Long, luscious lashes are the ultimate beauty goal. Not only do they make your eyes pop, but they also enhance your natural beauty. But, with great lashes comes great responsibility, and taking care of them is crucial for their longevity. Here are some tips to help you care for your lashes like a pro:

Remove your makeup gently: Use a gentle makeup remover to take off your eye makeup, avoiding harsh rubbing and tugging that can damage your lashes.

Brush your lashes: Use a clean spoolie brush to comb through your lashes daily, helping to distribute natural oils and prevent tangling.

Be gentle with your lash curler: When using a lash curler, use it gently and avoid using it too often, as it can damage your lashes.

Use a lash serum: Lash serums are a great way to promote lash growth and keep them healthy. Look for serums that are rich in biotin, peptides, and nourishing oils.

Be mindful of your mascara: Avoid using waterproof mascara too often, as it can be harsh on your lashes. Also, make sure to replace your mascara every few months to avoid bacteria buildup.

With these tips, you can maintain healthy and beautiful lashes that will leave everyone envious. So, take care of your lashes, and they will take care of you.

🌸အနံ့ဆိုးထွက်နေတဲ့ပန်းလေးတွေ မွှေးပျံ့လာစေပါတယ်။ 
🌸ဓမ္မတာလာနေစဉ်အတွင်း နာကျင်ကိုက်ခဲခြင်းနဲ့ ယားယံခြင်းတွေကို သက်သာစေပါတယ်။ 
🌸အဖြူဆင်းတာတွေ လျော့နည်းလာစေပါတယ်။ 
🌸ညိုမဲနေတဲ့နေရာတွေကို ပန်းနုရောင်အဖြစ် လှပလာစေပါတယ်။

တစ်ခဲလောက်သုံးလိုက်ရုံနဲ့တင် အရမ်းကိုထူးခြားသိသာလာစေတဲ့ Pink Soap လေးကို အပျိုလေးတွေအတွက်ဆိုရင် တစ်နေ့ကိုတစ်ကြိမ်ကနေ နှစ်ကြိမ် ပန်းလေးနဲ့အနီးတစ်ဝိုက်ကို ရေချိုးတဲ့အချိန်မှာ ဆေးကြောပေးနိုင်ပါတယ်။
အိမ်ထောင်ရှင်မမတွေအတွက်ဆိုရင် တစ်နေ့ကိုတစ်ကြိမ်ကနေ နှစ်ကြိမ် ပန်းလေးနဲ့အနီးတစ်ဝိုက်ကို နှစ်မိနစ်ခန့် ပေါင်းထားပြီးတော့ ဆေးကြောပေးလိုက်ရုံပါပဲ။ 

ပျိုမေလေးတို့ရဲ့တစ်နေ့တာမှာ ပန်းလေးတစ်ပွင့်လို မွှေးပျံ့ပြီး လွတ်လွတ်လပ်လပ်ပေါ့ပေါ့ပါးပါး ဖြတ်သန်းချင်တယ်ဆိုရင် Angel Pink Soap ကတော့ မရှိမဖြစ်ပါပဲနော်။ 💗

ခဏခဏစိတ်ညစ်ရတတ်တဲ့ မျက်နှာပေါ်ကအမဲစက်တွေနဲ့ဝက်ခြံတွေကိုလည်း Gluta Gold Collagen Serum လေးက တဖြည်းဖြည်းချင်းသက်သာလာစေပါတယ်။

😰 နွေရာသီမှာ ပူစီလေးကိုရော ဂရုစိုက်ဖြစ်ကြရဲ့လား ? 😰

တစ်နေ့ထက်တစ်နေ့ ပိုပိုပူလာတဲ့ နွေရာသီဥတုကြောင့် ချွေးထွက်များပြီး အသားအရေတွေ ယားယံတတ်ပါတယ်။ ဒီလိုအခြေအနေမျိုးမှာ ခန္ဓာကိုယ်ရဲ့အခြားနေရာတွေထက် ဂျိုင်းကြား၊ပေါင်ကြားတွေက ချွေးထွက်ပိုများတဲ့အတွက်ကြောင့် အနံ့ဆိုးနဲ့ယားယံခြင်းတွေကို ဖြစ်စေပါတယ်။ 

မိန်းမကိုယ်အနီးတစ်ဝိုက် ပူစီလေးမှာ အနံ့ဆိုးနဲ့ ယားယံခြင်းတွေဖြစ်လာတဲ့အခါ ကိုယ့်ကိုယ်ကို ယုံကြည်မှုတွေပျောက်ဆုံးစေနိုင်ရုံသာမက ကျန်းမာရေးအရကြည့်မယ်ဆိုရင်လည်း ဆိုးကျိုးတွေဖြစ်လာစေပါတယ်။ 😍

💁‍♀️ ဒါကြောင့် ပူစီလေးမှာ အနံ့ဆိုးတွေထွက်ပြီး ယားယံမှုတွေမဖြစ်ရလေအောင် ကြိုတင်ကာကွယ်တဲ့အနေနဲ့ Pink Soap လေးကို အသုံးပြုသင့်ပါတယ်။ 👌

Pink Soap လေးက - 

💗 အနံ့ဆိုးထွက်ခြင်း
💗 ယားယံခြင်း
💗 အဖြူဆင်းခြင်း 

အစရှိတဲ့ ပြဿနာတွေကို အကောင်းဆုံးဖြေရှင်းပေးနိုင်တာကြောင့် အခုလို ပူအိုက်လွန်းတဲ့နွေရာသီမှာ ပူစီလေးအတွက် လုံးဝမရှိမဖြစ်ပါပဲနော်။ 🥳

Pink Soap လေးက ယားယံတာ၊အနံ့ဆိုးထွက်တာမျိုးတွေမဖြစ်စေပဲ မွှေးရနံ့သင်းပျံ့တဲ့ပန်းလေးတစ်ပွင့်လိုမျိုးဖြစ်လာစေပါတယ်။ ဒါအပြင့် ညိုမဲတာမျိုးတွေဆိုရင်လည်း ရေရှည်စွဲသုံးပေးမယ်ဆိုရင် ပန်းရောင်သန်းတဲ့အလှအပလေးကို ရရှိလာစေမှာပါ။ 😍

အသုံးပြုနည်း - ဆပ်ပြာလေးကို အမြှုပ်ထလာအောင်လုပ်ပြီး ထွက်လာတဲ့အမြှုပ်လေးတွေနဲ့ စက္ကန့် ၄၀ ကနေ ၁ မိနစ်လောက်ပေါင်းတင်ပေးလိုက်ရုံပါပဲ။ ပြီးရင်သာမန်ဆပ်ပြာတွေအသုံးပြုသလို ရေဆေးချလိုက်ရင်ရပြီနော် ... 😘

❤️ အမျိုးသမီးအများစု ဖြစ်ပေါ်လေ့ရှိတဲ့ ခြောက်သွေ့ယားယံတာ၊ အရမ်းစိုစွတ်တာမျိုးတွေကို ကာကွယ်ပေးတယ်။

MASTER CLASS⁣ ✨
⁣
En estas clases el objetivo es que quienes no son profesionales del maquillaje, aprendan el paso a paso, técnicas, el por qué y para qué de cada producto para realizar looks completos, desde algo neutro, hasta uso de color, delineados y aplicaciones.⁣
⁣
Por otro lado para que quienes se dedican a maquillar desarrollen técnica de aplicación mucho más efectiva, tips y trucos para lograr looks profesionales y duraderos para todo tipo de rostros y pieles, uso de color y tendencias aplicado en sociales, pero sobretodo resaltar esos detalles que como maquilladores son clave en nuestros servicios. Les dejo aquí algunos de los temas de esta clase. Espero verlxs en la siguiente 🤍⁣
⁣
• Pieles perfectas ⁣
- Preparación de la piel y función de cada paso de skincare⁣
- Iluminación, neutralización y contornos de acuerdo a la anatomía facial⁣
- Técnicas de aplicación de productos líquidos, en crema y polvo⁣
- Pieles de larga duración e impermeables ⁣
• Look 1 de ojos: Anatómico⁣
- Un look que favorece a todo tipo y forma de ojos⁣
- Pestañas perfectas y naturales (técnica de rizado y aplicación de máscara de pestañas)⁣
- Tendencia de cejas⁣
• Look 2 de ojos: Miradas que enamoran⁣
- Transformar un look neutro integrando color y texturas ⁣
- Delineados - simetría y corrección ⁣
- Aplicación de pestañas⁣
- Integrar tendencias a sociales⁣, en este caso me inspiré en la #Trend #AngelPink 
• Labios: Construcción de texturas y acabos perfectos⁣
• Brochas clave en el kit (durante toda la sesión)⁣

It's insane the impact makeup can have on how you see yourself and how others perceive you. 

Whenever I put makeup on, I think about what I want to feel like that day, but unconsciously also think about who I'm meeting, where I'm heading, and what spaces I'll be occupying - and all these factors play a crucial role on my makeup, whether I consciously consider it or not. 

In the 1st photo, I emphasise my eyes, which are usually slightly obscured by my glasses, so this is a look I'd very comfortably (but still carry my personality!) wear to a professional meeting or a conference. 

The 2nd look is something I'd only wear to a march, to a party or to a makeup-related event - you wouldn't catch me outside with such bold makeup without good reason - because when I do, I often feel the judgement of people who aren't used to seeing such makeup, and that judgement weights heavy. 

The final photo is a femme-fatal look for me - the bold lip and the monotone face make me feel incredibly confident and sure that I'm ready for whatever comes my way. 

How does your makeup reflect how you're feeling daily? Do you consider where you'll be or who you'll be with? What makeup do you wear to feel most confident? Let me know!

As a social media advertiser my primary responsibility will be to help clients promote their products, services or brand on various media platforms, such as Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, LinkedIn, TikTok and more. My job will involve creating and managing ad campaigns, analyzing data, and optimizing ad performance to achieve the client's desired outcomes.
My asks may include:
Developing ad strategies: Understanding the client's goals, target audience, and budget to create an effective media advertising strategy.
Creating ad content: Developing engaging ad copy, images or videos that capture the audience's attention and motivate them to take action.
Managing ad campaigns: Setting up, launching, and monitoring social media ad campaigns to ensure they perform effectively and within budget.
Analyzing data: Tracking ad performance metrics such as click-through rates, engagement rates, and conversion rates to optimize ad performance and improve ROI.
Communicating with clients: Keeping clients updated on the progress of their ad campaigns and providing insights and recommendations on how to improve results.
Staying up-to-date: Keeping up-to-date with the latest media

caption:
#Eventos. MAC Cosmetics lanzó su Hyper Real Skincare, una línea de cosméticos faciales (para usar con y sin maquillaje), diseñada para equilibrar, retexturizar y mejorar la piel.
 
La línea incluye: el suero de hidratación, la crema hidratante y un aceite limpiador. Todos potenciados por la Pro-4 Power Infusion Matrix de MAC, que contiene extracto de peonía japonesa, niacinamida, ácido hialurónico y ceramidas reparadoras. La promesa es conseguir resultados inmediatos y duraderos. ¿Quién no quiere eso en su vida? 🙌🏻

 Para el lanzamiento de Hyper Real Skincare en @portazul_rd, MAC realizó dos encuentros donde artistas maquilladores, clientes e influencers participaron en un masterclass de maquillaje a cargo de Romero Jennings (@romerojennings), director de Makeup Artistry de MAC Cosmetics.

Nói đến đây không thể không gợi ý cho mọi người  routine dưỡng ẩm cùng với bộ sp skincare design for makeup Hyper Real này, làn da của mng sau khi apply sản phẩm sẽ ngay lập tức đón nhận sự căng mọng trên da, xịn lắm.

Vì tính chất công việc nên C phải thường xuyên makeup và đây cũng là một “ bảo bối“ mới toanh giúp C có đc làn da khoẻ và lớp makeup hoàn hảo cho cả ngày dài nè.

Hyper Real có thể giúp mng có được làn da rạng rỡ, cân bằng ẩm từ bên trong nhờ vào việc cấp ẩm đầy đủ cho da, củng cố hàng rào bảo vệ da, cải thiện bề mặt da, từ đó làn da của mng sẽ khỏe khoắn hơn và sẵn sàng với mọi lớp makeup từ tự nhiên đến lộng lẫy/full glam, bye bye nền mốc, trơn trượt luôn nhé 🥰.

Here’s my little MAC haul from the other day when I brought in 13 empties. The girl working at the @maccosmetics counter made my entire day - she was like “oh looks like you have 18 here so you can get three lipsticks!” and I was like “oh shit there should only be 13 in there” thinking I must have accidentally put 5 extras inside that I meant to keep. Then she was like “no…. you *gave* me 18 empties” 😉 I was like “OHHHH omg you’re the best” 😂 so she let me pick out a third one just to be nice and I was so excited! So I already knew I wanted Powder Kiss lipsticks which are my favorite matte lipstick formula, they give more of that blurred look but also have moisturizing properties so they don’t make my lips feel dry whatsoever. As someone with chapped lips and dry skin, I love that. I grabbed the shades Impulsive and Teddy 2.0 then chose the liquid lipstick version of the Powder Kiss formula as my third one. I haven’t tried those yet so I went with the shade Ferosh! as it reminds me of the shade Ripened, a favorite that was of course discontinued. 
I also picked up a new Mineralize Blush in the shade “Hey, Coral, Hey” making it my fifth one of these blushes, I love the glowy baked formula and would go as far to say this is my favorite powder blush formula. Lastly, I picked up a coconut Fix+ spray since I haven’t gotten any in a couple years now and it’s just a good staple to have. 
A huge shoutout to the girl at the MAC counter for being so awesome and kind ❤️ We were both so bummed out about the Back to MAC program ending. I’m just glad I got to try it once before it came to an end, though it’s a bummer that makeup artists and makeup lovers everywhere can no longer benefit from the program. They’re like “but you can still bring in the empties to recycle them” though I just don’t see that happening as often if there isn’t the free lipstick incentive. Hopefully they change their minds about that in the future! 💄🥲

My MAC lipstick collection! 💄 

I think this is 34 lip products here. The  orange one is a metallic gloss. I also have two more of the metallic glosses and a few random lipsticks I couldn’t find, but this is mostly it. I use this bag I’ve had since high school to store them, and it’s crazy that at one point I could fit my entire makeup collection into that bag. I have had some of these lippies since 2018 and plan on keeping the limited edition ones I have, like the Nicki Minaj and Aladdin. But I ended up clearing out 12 of the tubes in hopes of stopping at the MAC store later and getting 2 free lipsticks out of the deal. Unfortunately the Back to MAC program where 6 empties = 1 free lipstick ends tomorrow. Super bummed but never have gotten to try it and I could use some new ones. They keep discontinuing my faves over at @maccosmetics and it kinda sucks they’re ending the program. But since we’re going to Boston later, the MAC store is on the way! • Como não amar os batons MAC?
Desde que comecei a me interessar por maquiagens profissionais, eles eram o meu desejo de consumo e os meus 4 primeiros batons da Mac quem de meu de presente de aniversário foi o meu marido que na época era meu namorado, isso lá em meados do ano 2013/14 na saída da faculdade 💄 Nunca esqueço pq pra mim aquela foi uma grande prova de amor pq me dar 4 batons @maccosmeticsbrasil no auge dos lançamentos, incluindo o lendário Ruby woo ,Tinha que amar muito mesmo 💸😂 hahaha Ele tinha muito ciúmes dos batons que tinha me dado pq eu queria levar para todos os atendimentos que eu tava iniciando a fazer até pq eu queria mostrar para minhas clientes que eu tinhas os melhores batons do mercado! De la pra cá eu nunca mais comprei batons da Mac pq eu aproveitava o programa #backtomac que é um incentivo à reciclagem que eles fazem onde a cada 6 embalagens vazias, da direito a 1 batom da linha tradicional (resumi o que é o programa) mas infelizmente o Back to Mac vai acabar agora dia 31/03 🥹 e essa talvez tenha sido a minha última troca ate lá. Para mim o progaram era um super incentivo à reciclagem pq eu sou dessas que fico com pena de jogar até as caixa , imagina só as embalagens 🤭e para profissionais era uma mão na roda pq que comprávamos muito, usava e acabava rápido (principalmente base) e rápido juntava 6, garantindo um batom. Dessa vez consegui juntar 24 embalagens vazias e peguei 4 batons lindos (doía a maior quantidade de batons que consegui pegar de uma só vez), sendo um deles um que eu já tive e era um dos sua preferidos e agora tenho novamente que é o SPIRITI, HUG ME, PLUM DANDY, RUSSIAN RED, todos com textura mais cremosa. Ainda trouxe dois lápis para contorno que saiu com 15% pq foi no dia internacional da mulher. #batommac #spiritmac #hugmemac #plumdandymac #russianredmac

Not many are aware of the Back to MAC program endorsed by MAC Cosmetics globally. In order to promote sustainability, MAC encourages their customers to recycle 6 of their clean and emptied MAC containers in return for a free MAC lipstick!

All you gotta to is gather 6 of your unused or emptied out MAC products, clean them thoroughly then go to MAC near you to exchange them for a brand new and free MAC lipstick.

As stated in their website, these items are excluded from this program, so do take note:

💄Secondary packaging of any sort (paper box, plastic/cellophane wrapper, shopping bags, etc.)

💄Samples (sample containers, special/trial size products for promotional/seasonal kits)

💄 Cosmetic applicators/tools (disposables, puffs, sponges, scissors, spatulas, swabs, sharpeners, tweezers, curlers)

💄 Accessories (bags, belts, makeup cases, lashes, Blot Film)

This program will only be valid this 31st of March 2023, so there's still plenty of time for you to get your free MAC lipstick!

I decided to depot some of my Mac makeup to Back to Mac them. I know I have till the end of March to do so, but I wanted to depot them now since I have some free time this week as I've taken a few days of leave. It was easier than I thought it would be to remove the powder pans from the packaging of the Mac Studio Fix powder foundation, and I found the packaging of the Milk Makeup fits the pan perfectly. I never did much like the bulky packaging of the Mac powder foundation anyway, so this makes it easier to tote around in my purse. I'm currently using the top one that I stuck in the Milk Makeup compact, it's in the shade NC35 and it has a slight dip in it. I have used up two of them previously and it takes me over six months to use one up. The other two are in the shade NC30 but they don't look much different to me. 

I have also depotted a few lipsticks into empty lipstick containers, and I will take them to the Mac store today.

Back-To-M·A·C program 💄💋

A @maccosmeticshungary a környezetért vállalat felelősségeként 32 évvel ezelőtt elindította a Back-To-M·A·C programot. A program célja, hogy az eladott saját márkás termékek csomagolását begyűjtsék a vásárlóktól.

A részvételi adatok alapján a 32 év alatt több mint 80 tonna üres M·A·C csomagolást sikerült újrafeldolgozni, újrahasznosítani. 

És hogy te mit nyerhetsz a programban való részvétellel?! 👀🙃

Juttass vissza 6 darab kiürült csomagolást valamely M·A·C üzletbe és ajándékba kapsz egy általad választott M·A·C rúzst.

Ha esetleg nálad is van üres M·A·C csomagolás, ne habozz mielőbb visszavinni az egyik M·A·C üzletbe, mert a program 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟯.𝟬𝟯.𝟯𝟭-𝗶𝗴 érvényes. Jelenleg még nincs információ arról, hogy miként fog átalakulni a program.

This was my second Back to Mac lipstick that I got over a week ago but forgot to mention here. I handed in three compacts of the Studio Fix powder foundation after depotting the pans from the packaging (I wrote a post about it a few days ago) and added in three lipstick tubes after depotting them and placing them in empty lipstick tubes (again, I made some posts on how to do that as well a few days ago). I picked up the shade Business Casual in the lustreglass finish and I think it's a lovely shade. I was initially thinking of getting Taupe which is a matte shade, or Spirit which is a satin shade, but I ended up with this instead. The shiny lipstick is lovely, and the glossy finish packaging also looks very pretty. I'm glad I got the free lipstick. I wonder what offer they will have in place of the Back to Mac program though.

Over the last couple of years I've accumulated four Mac empty products (an eyeshadow palette, a powder foundation, a concealer and a lipstick), and I just needed two more. I thought I would depot two of my lipsticks that are over half used in order to get rid of the packaging (I hate hanging on to empty packaging, that's why I am unable to post monthly, let alone yearly, empties). So I removed what was left of the bullet of Mac Viva Glam I which is my favourite shade of red, and inserted it into an empty Kiko tube. It slid out very easily and fit into its new tube quite well. As for Lady Danger, I removed it from its tube (again, it came out very easily) and melted it into another Kiko tube mixed in with the brown shade it had in it. I didn't really like Lady Danger on its own in me, so I'm happy I was able to make a more workable shade for myself. 

So armed with six empty products, I  exchanged them for a lipstick. After swatching lipstick shades and repeatedly yet inadvertently picking up the shades I already own (clearly I have a type) till I got bored, I ended up repurchasing Mac Creme in Your Coffee, which was the third empty tube I had returned! It's a beautiful, wearable MLBB shade that I had really enjoyed, and I'm sure I will be able to use it up again. 

The lady there did confirm that the Back to Mac program is definitely ending by the end of March and she advised that I bring in any more empties I have to get a free lipstick while I can. I won't be able to have more than one lipstick empty by then, but I'm thinking of depotting some of the bullet lipsticks into empty packaging and I may be able to get another six empty packaging that way. 

#backtomac #maccosmeticsqatar #maccremeinyourcoffee

BACK-TO-M·A·C IS DONATING $100,000 TO PLASTICS FOR CHANGE THIS EARTH MONTH 🌎♻️. We are proud to support @plasticsforchange, a trusted source of fair trade-verified recycled plastic, to help reduce plastic waste while improving local communities: 

🌎GOING BEYOND CONTAINERS🌎 
Our plastic efforts are about more than recycling or recovering used M·A·C packaging. We are proud to donate $100,000 to Plastics for Change to enable the collection of over 550,000 pounds of plastic – equivalent to 12,500,000 plastic bottles – from our planet while supporting local communities. 

🌎SUPPORTING COMMUNITY🌎 
The money will help support approximately 200 collectors involved in the collection of plastic for one year with essential social services including education, healthcare and nutrition to families, and empowerment of women and girls. 

Visit our website to learn more about how to get involved in #BackToMAC and our overall environmental commitments.

Let me tell you about my shopping habit this past month. 

@target had a 20% off sale on their beauty products, so I got a replacement for my @honest_beauty Gentle Gel Cleanser, which is a staple for me, and the @cocokind Resurrection Polypeptide Cream, which is new to me but have been loving! I made a reel showing its texture; go check it out! 

Won a giveaway from @honeybeegardens with their Amethyst Crystal Infused Body Oil. My skin drinks it up, and it smells incredible. It's scented with essential oils of: lemon, rosemary, lavender, peppermint, and grapefruit.

I always bring this scent or the coconut 🥥  scented one when we go on vacay. 🥰🏖 Also got their Sweet Almomd scented Hand and Body Lotion which smells like literal dessert. The scent is new to me, but we've gone through countless tubes of their lotion in different scents. 

Went to @tjmaxx while I waited for my middle babe to get out of Robotics, and I almost never leave there empty handed. Their beauty section is like a treasure hunt. Spotted the @koparibeauty Coconut Hydrating Body Wash and I couldn't get over the beautiful pink bottle! It smells like sweet coconut and isn't drying. 
@alamaisonsoaps Honeysuckle Hand & Body Lotion is lightly scented and moisturizing without being greasy. 
Jumping on the manuka honey mask bandwagon with the @manukahealthusa Raw Manuka Honey. I've always masked with honey, but never Manuka. How many times did I say Manuka? Manuka. Manuka. 
Saw the @andalounaturals Turmeric + C Enlighten Serum and got nostalgic. I started using this back when it came in a green bottle many years ago. Who remembers? 

I didn't buy any makeup! Who am I?!

Uggg!! Anyone else have that horizontal crease between their brows?￼ 🤦🏻‍♀️ 
Did you know you can put these anywhere on your face? Not just under your eyes?! ￼

You might remember "The Botox incident" that's how ￼we refer to it! ￼If not, here's a quick recap… I got some Botox shots in my lower leg a few years back. I had a horrible reaction to it. About 3 weeks after the shots,
it started to paralyze most of my body. Literally taking away the little strength and movement that I have, ￼had trouble swallowing, trouble breathing & talking￼.
It was truly awful! And there was nothing I could do but basically wait the 3 months until it got out of my system. ￼Then try to regain the weakness that I lost. ￼Seriously, though only me… 🤷🏻‍♀️￼

What I learned from that are horrible experience is that I cannot rely on Botox in the future to help these fine lines and wrinkles! So liquid collagen, skin care, and these gold masks will have to do the trick!!!!￼🌟

Skincare Sunday: As an esthetician I am always researching skin care hacks. Here is a natural clay mask you can make in your own kitchen. 

How to: Mix bentonite clay (seen as an ingredient in #aztecclaymask ) and filtered water until consistency is a thick paste. Then pour some neem oil and Virgin bacuri butter about a teaspoon of each. Wash off with @shopapplytoskin cleanser and finish with the lotus daily moisturizer. 

APPLY TO SKIN for 20 minutes or until mask hardens on skin. I’m going to try this for 7 days and let you know how it goes. I’m trying to get rid of hyperpigmentation, acne and post acne marks. 

Benefits: 

Bentonite clay: People have used bentonite clay to remove impurities on the skin, such as oils, and toxins from the body for thousands of years. Bentonite clay is present in many skin products, but some people also add it to foods or drinks with the aim of relieving digestive issues or removing toxins from the body. 

Neem oil: from the neem tree in India. Able to balance oil production, heal wounds, stimulate collagen formation, reduce post-acne scars and minimise skin inflammation. It works as a natural alternative to heal the skin tissue from within and simultaneously reduces hyperpigmentation and scars.

Virgin Bacuri Butter: from the jungles of the Amazon in Brazil, derived from the seed of the bacuri fruit. Moisturizes and nourishes the skin, leaving it soft and supple. Provides anti-inflammatory and antioxidant benefits to the skin. And It helps to soothe and heal skin irritation and dryness.

Combine all three for the perfect natural DIY skincare mask to help all skin types. All ingredients are rich in magnesium, iron, and other vitamins. The bentonite clay takes away excess oils, while the neem boosts productivity when paired with other products, and the bacuri butter hydrates.

Sanktgallen Taproom〈本厚木〉
(@sanktgallen_taproom )

4月1日神奈川西部までお見舞いに。
元気そうで少しほっとしました。

帰る途中、
甚だ即物的な自分が恥ずかしいですが、
せっかくこっちまで来たんだし、と
連れ合いを巻き込んで本厚木にある
サンクトガーレンタップルームへ。

こちらは日本のクラフトビールの元祖、
サンクトガーレンブリュワリーの直営店。

毎年エイプリルフールビールを発表し、本当に製品にしてしまうお茶目な一面もある大好きなブリュワリーです。

今年は「オ・ウンゴルIPA」。
サッカーの試合でオウンゴールが入ると

「オ・ウンゴル選手が決めた〜!!」

みたいにイジるネット文化があるそうで。
それに引っ掛けて、
「オ・ウンゴル選手とスポンサー契約を締結」したサンクトガーレンが同選手のビールを4月1日に発売。

まずはそのオ・ウンゴルIPAで乾杯！
苦味のビシッと効いた昔ながらのIPAです。
昨今はフレーバーの効いた飲みやすいIPAも多数ありますが(そっちも大好きですけどね)、骨太でどっしり旨い。

どうやら後発のIPAと区別するために、昔ながらのIPAはクラフトビール界隈で「OG IPA」と表現したりするのだそうですが、
まさかの、
サッカー用語「OG=オウンゴール」とかかっている!!

おしゃれな嘘満載のエイプリルフールビール、堪能いたしました。

他のビールもおつまみもとても美味しかった。
素敵な止まり木で一息つけました。
本当にありがとう。

Using an old photo because these days I am just too tired to document my life lol. #TDOV is supposed to be a day of hope and joy for our community, specifically for our youth. To be able to see that our life can extend beyond the immediate and that there can be joy and happiness and success in our lives to come. 

But lately the more it goes on, the more the cis community begins to co-opt it, to exploit trans folks and shrug off their guilt in contributing to this violent and oppressive society. Corporations make cute little graphics and allies share cartoons in performative allyship, but let me ask you this. You want us to be visible, and by visible you and I both know you mean vulnerable. But what is visibility without concrete safety measures in place before hand? You live for the trans girls, taking our language and our behaviors. You say we're so brave to be our authentic self, but what you really mean is that you're not passing, but you're so brave for trying.

Do you only support and comment on passing people? On conventionally beautiful 'girls'? Or the skinny ones or the muscular 'boys'? How many have you told me "I just don't get why ___ would try and wear a skirt" or "I can't tell if that's a boy or girl but werq!" Our transness isn't decided by your comfortability and closed minded understandings of gender. 

Healthcare and mutual aid is only extended when trans/nb folks bare their souls and their trauma, reliving it again and again to "tell their brave stories" for you to relish in the satisfaction of helping someone you intrinsically think is less than you. 

We are not a circus, we do not dance when you ask us to.

And don't for one second think I don't see those who share "aesthetic" TDOV memes/graphics but haven't mentioned a single one of the 450+ ANTI TRANS bills. 

And if you try and lump me in with the drag queen bills I will ruin you. Is it important? Yes. Nuance is important. 

It never ended with gay marriage. It never even started there.
Happy #TransDayOfVisbility to all my friends, family, and chosen family in the trans community! I am in constant awe of your beauty, bravery, and talent!

“Growing up, I always had an interest in science and mathematics. When I was a kid, I wanted to be an astronaut and then an engineer. After I took my first coding class in high school, I jumped headfirst into learning anything I could about programming and higher-level math.

By the time I got to college, a lot was changing in my life. My college introduced a data science bachelor’s degree when I was a sophomore and I ended up making the decision to switch my major, all while a pandemic was starting around the world. Starting a new degree program while professors were trying to figure things out was a really weird time for me.

Thankfully, as the COVID-19 shutdown began, I had a really good support system within my family, my swimming teammates, professors and friends. At this time, I was also really questioning my gender identity and how I felt comfortable presenting myself.

When I finally made it to my senior year of college, I had already come out as a transgender man. But I also had to make another big decision about what I was going to do after college. I didn’t know if I wanted to continue my work by doing research in graduate school or heading straight into a job. One of my professors mentioned the work they do at the Lab, so I looked more into APL.

It was then that I realized that APL’s work was what I was looking for; and not only that, but it was a place where staff members’ inclusivity and diversity was important.

Being trans is extremely difficult right now, which is why finding a workplace that is supportive and caring is everything I could ask for in a community. I am a new staff member at the Lab, and everyone that I have interacted with is amazing. Finding where you belong is super important and my parents ask me all the time if I’ve made the right decision – I always say yes. I am as happy as I could be with a supportive partner and a job that gives me amazing opportunities and problems to tackle every day.”

Hal Stewart is a data scientist in #JHUAPL’s Asymmetric Operations Sector.

From the start of human history trans people have existed. From the start of human history it was accepted. The United States government is moving backwards, and moving society backwards. Trans people aren't going away no matter how hard you try. The conservatives that are trying to pass legislation against trans people don't care about the facts. The fact of the matter is that science has, and always will support trans people. You cannot erase us. Trans people exist whether you like it or not, and you cannot hide us from society. Our community has always won, and and and will continue to win. They fear what they do not understand. Instead of sitting down and having a conversation of education, and sit down and have a conversation of hate. There are eight BILLION people on this planet and trans people make up less than 1% of that. My question for United States law makers is why do you care. Because of what Missouri law makers have done, I will never get the opportunity to live the rest of my teenage years the way that makes me free. Missouri law makers will never understand how dysphoria feelings and how gut wrenching it is. Everyday since I was 11, I've wanted to take my own life just to see if there was even a fraction of a possibility that in my next life I'd be born a male. Everyday of my entire life I've felt that I do not own my body. That my body is not mine. My body deserves someone who can love it in the way I cannot. HRT is not mutilating my body, it's saving my life. Surgery is not mutilating my body, it's saving my life. I will never get to know how it feels to have a male childhood. I will never get to know how happy I could've been and how much of my sadness and anger towards myself could've been prevented. I know there a thousands of kids my age who feel the same, and not all of us are lucky to survive the emotional torment that is our existence. What the US government is doing is killing our children. Trans people are human beings. We all bleed red.

To my fellow trans people, the fight is not over. History has proved time and time are again, we will survive.

Laut verschiedenen Schätzungen leben zwischen zwanzig- und achtzigtausend Menschen in Deutschland, die sich als Transperson identifizieren. Der Alltag vieler dieser Personen ist beschwerlich: Ob durch ein veraltetes #TSG, durch die Mauern in den Köpfen vieler Menschen oder durch die Angst, #transphobeGewalt erleiden zu müssen. Gewalt an Transpersonen dominierte im vergangenen Jahr mehrfach die Schlagzeilen. Die medial präsenten Angriffe haben in den Öffis, den eigenen vier Wänden und sogar am Rande eines #CSD stattgefunden. Der heutige #TransDayOfVisbility ist daher eine gute Gelegenheit, auf den Missstand transphober Gewalt aufmerksam zu machen und die #Vielfalt und Toleranz zu feiern. So haben wir es heute im Bundesinnenministerium getan. Das Ministerium hat eine Anlaufstelle für seine Beschäftigten geschaffen, die informiert und sensibilisiert. Vielen Dank!
